    {
      "id": "person:speaker-01",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Nora"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:8728b1a6cf6337c9",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 272,
        "char_start": 6,
        "episode_id": "d04b0413-4fbe-5d89-b3e8-774bbc15a3c4",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Welcome back to Long Horizon Notes. Today is a debate \u2014 one question, two people who genuinely disagree. I'm joined by Daniel Cho, who runs a low-cost index practice, and Scott Bessent, a hedge fund manager who's built his career on concentrated bets. Welcome, both.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 6000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 0,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p05_e04.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-02",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Daniel Cho"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:cab4fef8c70ce51a",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 332,
        "char_start": 285,
        "episode_id": "d04b0413-4fbe-5d89-b3e8-774bbc15a3c4",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Thanks, Nora. Happy to be the boring one today.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 12000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 6000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p05_e04.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "person:speaker-03",
      "properties": {
        "name": "Scott Bessent"
      },
      "type": "Person"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:37b18715b7236c72",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 389,
        "char_start": 348,
        "episode_id": "d04b0413-4fbe-5d89-b3e8-774bbc15a3c4",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-03",
        "text": "And I'll be the reckless one, apparently.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p05_e04.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:5ea7b427accdb7cd",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 521,
        "char_start": 396,
        "episode_id": "d04b0413-4fbe-5d89-b3e8-774bbc15a3c4",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Before we dig in \u2014 today's episode is sponsored by Vanguard. Vanguard pioneered low-cost index funds. Try vanguard.com today.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p05_e04.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:c134f56cfc92185d",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 675,
        "char_start": 521,
        "episode_id": "d04b0413-4fbe-5d89-b3e8-774bbc15a3c4",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Here's the proposition: for an ordinary investor, is diversification the answer \u2014 or a way to hide from decisions you should be making? Daniel, you first.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p05_e04.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:a8c86960afd73962",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 927,
        "char_start": 688,
        "episode_id": "d04b0413-4fbe-5d89-b3e8-774bbc15a3c4",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "For an individual investor, diversification is the closest thing to a free lunch that exists. You give up almost nothing, and you remove the single biggest way people ruin themselves \u2014 one position going to zero at the worst possible time.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 36000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 30000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p05_e04.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    }
  ],
